Durban -  A truck driver and his assistant are entrapped in their vehicle after it collided into a wall in Pinetown on Monday. Garrith Jamieson, Rescue Care paramedics spokesperson, said the driver allegedly lost control of the truck on Gillitts Road near the intersection with Mariannhill Road and colluded into the wall of a building. "The driver and  his two assistants were entrapped in the wreckage. One of the assistants was extricated from the truck cab. The Durban Fire Department and paramedics have stablised the two others. The jaws of life has been used to free the men from the wreckage. The cause of the collision will be investigated by police,"Jamieson said. The Lenmed 1 helicopter landed to assist in transporting the injured men to a nearby hospital. Jamieson said the traffic has been severely affected on the route while emergency vehicles attend to the injured. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
